From: OpenWrt Community <openwrt@example.com>
Date: Sat, 24 May 2025 00:00:00 +0000
Subject: ath11k: add 6 GHz LPI fallback rule to world regulatory domain

When ath11k receives a non-EXT regulatory event (WMI_REG_CHAN_LIST_CC_EVENTID)
is_ext_reg_event is false and ath11k_reg_build_regd() produces a regdomain
with no 6 GHz rules.  cfg80211 then marks every 6 GHz channel DISABLED for
the self-managed wiphy, blocking any AP or STA on those channels.

This happens on chips where current_cc_support = false (e.g. QCN9074 PCIe)
because ath11k_reg_notifier() responds to user country-code hints with
WMI_INIT_COUNTRY_CMDID, which triggers a non-EXT response instead of the
EXT event that carries 6 GHz rules.

Add a conservative 6 GHz LPI rule (NO_IR, indoor-only, 30 dBm ceiling)
to ath11k_world_regd so that the fall-back world domain keeps 6 GHz
channels usable.  Proper per-country power limits are still applied
whenever the firmware does supply a 6 GHz EXT event (which takes
precedence via regulatory_set_wiphy_regd on new_regd updates).

Signed-off-by: OpenWrt Community <openwrt@example.com>
---
 drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/reg.c | 8 +++++++-
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+), 1 deletion(-)

--- a/drivers/net/wireless/ath/ath11k/reg.c
@@ -14,18 +14,24 @@
 					  NL80211_RRF_NO_IR)
 #define ATH11K_5GHZ_5725_5850    REG_RULE(5725 - 10, 5850 + 10, 80, 0, 30,\
 					  NL80211_RRF_NO_IR)
+/* 6 GHz LPI fallback: conservative indoor-only rule covering the full
+ * unlicensed 6 GHz band.  Used when firmware does not supply 6 GHz rules.
+ */
+#define ATH11K_6GHZ_5925_7125    REG_RULE(5925 - 10, 7125 + 10, 320, 0, 30,\
+					  NL80211_RRF_NO_IR)

 #define ETSI_WEATHER_RADAR_BAND_LOW		5590
 #define ETSI_WEATHER_RADAR_BAND_HIGH		5650
 #define ETSI_WEATHER_RADAR_BAND_CAC_TIMEOUT	600000

 static const struct ieee80211_regdomain ath11k_world_regd = {
-	.n_reg_rules = 3,
+	.n_reg_rules = 4,
 	.alpha2 =  "00",
 	.reg_rules = {
 		ATH11K_2GHZ_CH01_11,
 		ATH11K_5GHZ_5150_5350,
 		ATH11K_5GHZ_5725_5850,
+		ATH11K_6GHZ_5925_7125,
 	}
 };
